<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1868-02-17T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1868-02-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="35" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d35">
                        <head><persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Adams</persName></head>
                        <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram per cable.]</seg></opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Washington,</hi></placeName>
                                <date calendar="gregorian" when="1868-02-17"><hi rend="italic">February</hi> 17, 1868.</date></dateline></opener>
                        <p>Is counsel, special or otherwise, employed for Nagle, and how?
                            Telegraph.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed></closer>
                        <postscript>
                            <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Charles Francis Adams,</hi> Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c., &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi></p>
                        </postscript>
                    </div>
